The paper deals with the problem of assigning multiple mobile robots to goals on transport networks, which is a classic problem in robotics and automation. The use of redundant robots to provide resilience to uncertainty is a common approach in robotics, which suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also proposes a method that makes use of mathematical optimization and machine learning techniques to solve the problem, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The paper also deals with the problem of uncertainty, which is a common issue in control and automation, suggesting that it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper proposes a greedy algorithm and derives sub-optimality bounds, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
